They work great but they fit kind of weird on the head.
review_text: Rather than sitting right on the head, these have too much curvature to them which makes them look kind of strange.  It's unfortunate because other than that they are decent headphones.They seem very durable and are other wise comfortable.  The sound quality and noise cancellation are decent but obviously don't match up with higher end ones, but since these cost a lot less, it's an obvious trade-off.The Amazon branding isn't too prominent and the controls are pretty easy to use.  We are used to headphones that you tap on to pause, answer a call, activate/deactivate noise cancellation and these require you to hunt for the button with your finger.  If you aren't used to the ones with the tap method, getting used to these is probably pretty easy, for us it wasn't.They would make a great pair as a spare or ones to use on your commute on a train/bus, or even at the gym.  Since they aren't Beats/Apple/Sony/Sennheiser/etc. you are much less likely to have them swiped.  They'd also be great for a child.Overall we feel they are a decent value for the money, though there are pairs on Amazon that offer more functionality for a similar price.  Those usually aren't name brands and since we are assuming that Amazon is doing a lot of work to vet these, you'd likely be better with these vs. some company that nobody has ever heard of.Other than the overly curved headband part, we are happy with them.  The battery life is as advertised and for that reason as well as the reasons above we give them a 4/5 star rating and our recommendation.

review_title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Very good noise cancellation and listening experience at a relatively low price.
review_text: I got these a few weeks ago and wanted to wait until I had used them for a while to give a review.Overall, these are really good headphones with nice noise cancellation. At the time I received my pair via Vine, the retail price was $35. I think these headphones are more like a steal at that price.My first thought when I put on the Amazon pair was that they were *really* comfortable. The ear cups fit mostly around my ear, but I don't get any pain or fatigue from wearing them. They also stay in place, even when I sweat from housework. They have paired easily with all my devices - phone, home pc, work laptop. I have only listened to audio and have not used any phone capabilities, so I can't comment on that. They are also relatively light compared to my other full-sized headset and I really like that. Even though my other set is an older pair of high-quality Bose headphones, the good qualities of this Amazon headset have had me reaching for it instead.Noise Cancellation: This is my first pair of headphones with noise cancelling. I was shocked at how much it dampened noise around me. It definitely improved my listening experience through some noisy neighbors. The sound quality is good. I can clearly hear the things I want to hear. I'm not an audiophile so I can't describe the audio in those kinds of terms.Battery Life: I have not worn/used the headphones for the stated amount of hours, but I can say that I have been able to go several days without charging them. I typically wear headphones all day on the weekends, and I have definitely been able to listen at 8 hour stretches with no problem. I have no issue believing that the battery life is as described.Buttons/Interface: The interface is pretty limited, which makes sense with the lower price point. It has a round, flat power on/off button. The noise cancellation button is also round but has a raised sound wave on it to help differentiate it by feel. I can typically tell the difference, but due to some health problems, I have been experiencing some neuropathy (tingling, numbness) in my fingers and that makes it hard to make sure i am pressing the right button. I may put a drop of glue or something else next to the power button to help guide me by touch on those days.Small Nitpicks:The voice announcing power on/power off is very loud. It is static and cannot, as far as I know, be changed or turned off. If I have been listening at lower volumes, sometimes it blasts my ears a little.My main "problem" is that there is no way to tell how much battery life is left. There is no screen on the headset, and my Samsung phone doesn't pick up the remaining battery percentage when I connect to it. My computer will. Along with the lower price point, there is no app to use with these which might tell the remaining battery. An app would make the product more expensive, so again, I understand why there isn't one. I will just have to listen for the announcement, I guess.Overall, these are a solid 4.5 stars. If they are in your price range, get them. They're great as a primary or even backup pair of headphones.

5.0 out of 5 stars

review_text: I have tried a $600 product, and also a product at a comparable price. With the $600 product I got "ear suck" where my ears felt pressure when the noice canceling ANC feature was on. After doing some reading about this, I assumed I wouldn't be able to tolerate any noice canceling. I bought these simply to listen to music with the ANC turned off. To my delight and great surprise, I do not get ear suck with these!!! In addition, they are very comfortable, fold into many positions which make them work for just about any headphone case out there, I can wear them for hours without getting a headache (not true for other headphones like ear muffs for mowing the lawn). The sound quality (both treble and base and mids) is impressive for the price point. I'm very happy listening to music (classical, Hamilton, Celtic, opera (Pavarotti, Montsserrat Caballe...) as well as audiobooks and text to voice. I am musically trained and have also run an Alan and Heath GL 4200 sound system and I am pretty happy with the sound quality. They aren't supreme, but I didn't expect them to be at this price and I wasn't expecting to be this happy with the sound because of the price point. I bought these for studying and they greatly enhance my ability to study with noice in the environment. They pair very easily with any of my Bluetooth devices without difficulty. I think they are incredibly well designed, and the fit is very comfortable for me. If you want a good pair of headphones without paying an absurd amount of money--BUY THESE!

review_title:
4.0 out of 5 stars
Great Value ANC Headphones with Awkward Controls
review_text: Trends are funny. Everyone moved from bulky headphones to tiny earbuds, and now big over-ear cans are back. I still prefer earbuds for portability, but these headphones show why some people are switching back.What Stands OutPrice & Features ‚Äì For the cost, you get excellent active noise cancellation (ANC), a transparency mode to let outside sound in, and the ability to pair with more than one device.Battery Life ‚Äì About 35 hours with ANC on easily outlasts most wireless earbuds, making them perfect for long flights.Hybrid Use ‚Äì They include a wired adapter so you can plug into an airplane seatback screen. This is something earbuds can‚Äôt always handle.Comfort & Style ‚Äì Cushioned ear cups make them comfortable, though they can get warm over time. The matte black looks good if you don‚Äôt mind the bulk.Drawbacks & Suggestions:All the controls - volume, power, ANC toggle, and multi-function buttons, are crammed onto the right ear cup. While wearing them, it‚Äôs hard to tell which is which, so I often have to take the headphones off to adjust settings. Separating the buttons or adding distinct textures would fix this.If you can live with the awkward controls, these are a solid, affordable choice for long-lasting noise-canceling headphones with the bonus of wired playback when you need it.

review_title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Budget headphones that punch way above their price
review_text: I got these Amazon Basics noise-cancelling headphones because I didn‚Äôt want to drop a fortune on a big-name pair, and honestly, I‚Äôm impressed. The sound is clear and full, bass is solid without being overwhelming, and the noise cancelling actually does its job. It‚Äôs not ‚Äúworld disappears completely‚Äù level, but it takes the edge off background noise so I can focus, whether I‚Äôm working or just zoning out with music.The first time I used them was on a long train ride, and I couldn‚Äôt believe how much quieter it felt. The rumble and chatter faded way down, and I was able to actually enjoy my playlist without cranking the volume. At home, I‚Äôve been using them during work calls, and the fit is comfortable enough that I forget I have them on, even after a couple of hours.Battery life is another big win. I charged them once at the beginning of the week, and with ANC on, I‚Äôve been using them daily without running out of juice. Knowing I can get 35‚Äì45 hours depending on settings means I don‚Äôt have to babysit the battery.If you‚Äôre looking for affordable, reliable headphones with surprisingly good sound and noise cancelling, these are a solid pick. They may not have the fancy brand name, but they definitely get the job done, and then some.

review_title:
4.0 out of 5 stars

review_text: I work from home and needed a reliable pair of noise-canceling headphones to block out household noise. The sound clarity is great, and the bass is comparable to higher-end models. The noise-canceling is decent but not the strongest. Definitely need to pump up the volume to block the noise which I do not want to do. They‚Äôre comfortable, though even at the shortest adjustment they feel a little long on my head/ears. The build feels a bit plastic compared to other brands, but time will tell if they hold up . I appreciate that they come with a USB-C charger and an auxiliary cable, to plug in directly. The aux cord is especially handy for meetings directly on my laptop. Call clarity is good, and the long battery life is a huge bonus for someone like me who forgets to charge often. Overall, a solid choice for the price.

review_title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Reliable Quality‚ÄîExactly What I Expect from Amazon Basic
review_text: If it's an Amazon Basics product, I know it's going to be good‚Äîand these headphones did not disappoint! The sound quality is excellent, with rich bass and clear highs, and the hybrid active noise cancelling works surprisingly well, especially at this price point.They're super comfortable for long listening sessions, and the battery life is impressive‚Äî35 hours with ANC on and up to 45 hours with it off! Bluetooth connectivity is smooth and stable, and the over-ear fit helps block out ambient noise even without ANC.Whether I‚Äôm working, traveling, or just relaxing, these headphones deliver consistent performance. Great value, great quality‚ÄîAmazon Basics nailed it again!

review_title:
4.0 out of 5 stars
Really nice sound quality and good noise cancelling
review_text: I have to say these are really nice headphones since I've been using them. The sound quality is really good. It does look like though that these headphones don't produce audio past 44,100 KHZ. I would have liked to seen at least 48,000 KHZ. It can also hit pretty good mid range and low end bass levels. I'm definitely happy with the bass levels it can hit. In windows you can also do multiple adjustments adjusting the bass levels. The noise cancelling feature works really good too. I've notice higher frequency noises do seem to slip through though. The transparency feature does works okay if you want to hear things around you. I've never really had a pair of headphones though where the transparency feature works very good. Also ear cushions are pretty comfortable. I do wish though they were a bit on the bigger side though. My ear basically fills up the entire opening and the cushions push against them a little bit. Range is really good too. I have used other BT headphones and have had connectivity issues with them in my house if I get too far away. With these headphones I haven't experienced the connectivity issues like weak or dropping connections. The overall build quality of the headphones feels good too. These don't feel cheap at all. I would dare to say almost as good as a pair of Bose. Not quite but almost. Overall these are a pretty good pair of noise cancelling headphones and I don't think you'll be disappointed in trying these out.

review_title:
4.0 out of 5 stars
Headphones that mask low end droning noise
review_text: I‚Äôve owned a wide range of headphones from $20 beaters to $500 sets, but this is my first pair with active noise cancelling. Overall, I‚Äôd call these decent for the price with a few quirks worth pointing out.Pairing was simple, hold the power button, select them on your device, and you‚Äôre ready to go. Button functions are straightforward, and I was surprised to find you can even take calls through the headphones. I haven‚Äôt tested call quality yet, but it‚Äôs a nice option to have.There are three modes: NC on, NC off, and Transparent. In normal conversation level background noise, the NC effect was subtle. The real difference came when I tested them against a loud fan. The low frequency hum dropped noticeably, which seems to be the kind of sound these headphones are designed to reduce. Transparent mode works best with music paused, letting you hear voices and room sounds through the built in mics.The sound quality differs across modes.NC ON: Boosts the low end heavily. It helps mask noise but makes music sound a bit muddy. Fun for casual listening, not for accuracy.Transparent: Cuts lows sharply to prioritize outside sound, but with music playing you still won‚Äôt hear much of your surroundings.NC Off: Surprisingly the weakest mode. Flatter, thinner sound compared to NC On. Useful only if you‚Äôre stretching battery life.Overall, these headphones do a fair job cutting droning, low frequency noise but won‚Äôt give you silence. The sound signature changes a lot between modes, and I found NC On the most listenable even with its boomy bass. If you want perfectly balanced audio, you may prefer a non NC set at this price. But if you‚Äôre looking for entry level noise cancelling that works against fans, engines, or other steady rumbles, these aren‚Äôt a bad buy.

review_title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Inexpensive High-Quality Sound, Hybrid Active Noise Cancelling Headphones
review_text: These Amazon Basics hybrid active noise cancelling headphones are anything but "basic." They sound great, the active noise cancelling is good, but doesn't cancel everything. I was using them at my kitchen table listening to music with the game on in the other room, and I could still hear some of it. However, for under $40, these are a steal compared to something from Bose or Beats or Sony that are routinely $100-200 for a similar set. The size is a little large on the smallest setting so it might not be the best fit with young people or someone with a smaller head. You can disable the hybrid ANC and without a recharge, they can play your music, audiobooks, podcasts for at least 45 hours of playback with ANC turned off. These are a high-quality over-the-ear headphones. The one feature missing in this set is a carrying bag, which is not included. Also, there is a charger included for these headphones. You do get a charging USB-A cable that you can plug into a charger. There is also an auxiliary cable included that you could plug into your device if you don't have bluetooth on that device. Otherwise, these premium headphones are great for a cost conscious consumer looking for the quality of the top audio sets.

review_title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Thump and Go
review_text: I am pleasantly surprised by these Amazon Basics headphones.  Although the build is plastic, it's well done.  Nothing garish here, just a nice, classical look.  The fit is comfortable and the pads are soft.  I guess my only quibble here is a problem common to all closed-back headphones:  they get hot to wear for long periods of time.  So what.  They charged quickly;  all the control buttons operate normally.Now to the sound.  It's terrific for a budget set of cans.  I acknowledge that I use an EQ program to tweak my phones.  This one is no exception.  Everyone's taste is different in these matters.  With equalization the bass is just right...thumpy but not overly done.  Trebles and mids are well balanced.  Sound stage and imaging are great for this price point.Will you get your money's worth?  Yep.  Pick 'em up if you are looking for good sound at a reasonable price.  These are better than a whole slew of similarly priced models.

Within weeks, my beloved headphones dangled like a broken promise.My wife, ever generous, offered hers. ‚ÄúSurely,‚Äù I thought, ‚Äúher pair will be different.‚Äù Spoiler: it wasn‚Äôt. The same cursed crack appeared, right on schedule. I‚Äôm currently in the ‚Äúdenial‚Äù stage of grief, watching them slowly self-destruct with every listen.The sound quality? Surprisingly decent. The durability? About as sturdy as a plastic greenhouse in a hurricane.I still love my Soundcore earbuds‚Äîthey‚Äôve stayed faithful. But as for the Q30s‚Ä¶ I‚Äôll be moving on. These noise-cancelling earbuds strike a rare balance between smart tech, comfort, and sound quality that makes them a standout in their price range.Noise Cancelling That Actually WorksThe P30i‚Äôs noise cancelling is impressively strong and adaptive. Whether I‚Äôm on a noisy commute, walking through a busy store, or just trying to focus at home, these earbuds create a bubble of calm. The volume control is spot on. The smart ANC adjusts beautifully to different environments, and it‚Äôs not just marketing fluff‚Äîit‚Äôs real, effective tech.Sound That Punches Above Its WeightThe audio is rich, clear, and surprisingly dynamic. Bass is deep without being muddy, mids are crisp, and highs sparkle just enough. Podcasts, music, calls‚Äîit all sounds fantastic. I‚Äôve even had people comment on how clear my voice is during calls, thanks to the built-in mics.Comfort Meets DurabilityThey‚Äôre lightweight and fit snugly without pressure, even during long listening sessions. The build feels solid, and the case is compact yet sturdy‚Äîeasy to toss in a bag without worry. Battery life is excellent, easily lasting through a full day of use with juice to spare.Smart Features That Feel ThoughtfulPairing is seamless, and the app gives you control over EQ settings and ANC modes. It‚Äôs intuitive and adds a layer of customization that makes these feel-like premium earbuds. Plus, the touch controls are responsive and easy to learn.Perfect for Treating YourselfWhether you‚Äôre upgrading your own gear or looking for a thoughtful tech gift for yourself, the P30i delivers. It‚Äôs sleek, practical, and packed with features that feel like they belong in a much more expensive product.
